"26:39:5" : {s: 26, a: 39, w: 5, r: "جمع", t: "مُّجْتَمِعُونَ", l: "مُّجْتَمِعُون", lc: 1, tl: "muj'tamiʿūna", lb: "একত্রিত",e: "assemble", b: "সমবেত হচ্ছ", f: 1, rm: "To collect or gather, bring together, to contract, assemble or congregate, unite or connect or form a connection, bring into a state of union, reconcile or conciliate, put on a thing [such as clothing article], to compose/arrange/settle, to pray in congregation, determine/resolve/decide upon a thing, agree or unite in opinion, prepare or make a thing ready, dry up a thing, conspire or league with another, coexist with one, to be compact/compressed/contracted, exert ones energy, to compromise or comprehend or contain, enter or go into, to meet or be in company with another."},
